Andile Mngxitama Let’s get this right. Sports must be run by former professional players with imput from current players, the Dept of Arts and Culture by artists, hospitals by doctors and other medical professionals. Elected politicians must create the conditions for professionals to do their jobs. They must create the legal and policy framework to let people with the know-how to thrive. Politicians can set targets and monitoring systems to ensure results. We can’t continue like this. Andile Mngxitama is the President of Black First Land First (BLF) a radical black consciousness organization. When using any of Black Opinion’s content, partly or in full, kindly always provide an active hyperlink to the original material.